</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elhanamistfall>ElhanaMistfall</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.mistfits.com/tgrobb/elhanaportsmall.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crosslegged, quiet, and<br> filled with doom.</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/5/02 6:26:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=78.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> I don't know what other experience you've had, but if you are going to play a cleric it is best that you take your time with the class.  FV has a moderate to small server population, so if you don't know how to hunt solo as a cleric, you may have trouble getting experience.<br>
<br>
A place like High Hold Keep will probably always be busy, so you shouldn't have any trouble getting a group there.  Alternately, Paludal Cavern is also a popular spot.<br>
<br>
If you get comfortable with soloing, Unrest would probably be a good place because you can hunt on your own or join a pickup group depending on who's around. <br>
<br>
I'd take Talkdaydar's message to heart though. This can be a tough server.  You might have more fun if you play a class that can take care of themselves a little bit more efficiently. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
